The paper introduces a class of auto-encoder neural networks tailored to data from the natural exponential family, which includes count data. The architectures are inspired by convolutional generative models with sparsity constraints, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses discriminative training, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves optimization procedures, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT).
